==English==
===Noun===
'''fiver'''
# {{UK}} A slang term for a five pound note
# {{US}} A slang term for a five dollar bill
# A clenched fist
# A [[Zaydi]] Shiite Muslims, who disagrees with the majority of Shiites on the identity of the Fifth Imam
# A fictional rabbit in the novel ''[[w:Watership Down|Watership Down]]'' 
# A person who gives five percent of their income and/or five hours a week of their time to charity (a reduction of the ten percent [[tithe]] called for in the book of [[Deuteronomy]])
# A math game is played on a 5x5 grid [http://www.math.com/students/puzzles/fiver/fiver.html]
# A short written parody of a television episode, movie, play, or video game. [http://www.fiveminute.net]


